  "title": "Pre-Sales Engineer (Palo Alto / Network Security)",
  "description": "<h3>🔑 <strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Collaborate closely with the sales and product teams to align technical solutions with business needs</li>\n  <li>Lead and deliver Proof-of-Concept (POC) sessions to demonstrate product capabilities, especially in <strong>Palo Alto Networks</strong> security solutions</li>\n  <li>Prepare tailored technical proposals and solution architecture documents</li>\n  <li>Conduct engaging presentations, workshops, and demos for clients and partners</li>\n  <li>Provide both <strong>pre-sales</strong> and <strong>post-sales</strong> technical support throughout the solution lifecycle</li>\n  <li>Stay updated with emerging security technologies and trends to recommend relevant solutions</li>\n  <li>Contribute to internal knowledge sharing and solution development initiatives</li>\n  <li>Perform other duties as assigned to support the team</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>🎓 <strong>Requirements</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related fields</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years’ experience in <strong>IT Security</strong>, preferably in a pre-sales or solution consultant capacity</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of <strong>Security Architecture</strong>, OSI &amp; TCP/IP models, and networking protocols</li>\n  <li>Hands-on experience with <strong>firewalls, intrusion prevention systems (IPS)</strong>, and related security technologies</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with <strong>Palo Alto Networks</strong> solutions is highly desirable</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We appreciate your interest and look forward to reviewing your application. Due to high application volume, only shortlisted candidates will be contacted — thank you for your understanding!</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>WeCruit Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel: Tan Soon Hock (Steven) | Registration No. R1109889</p>",
